his reporter days.In his investigation, Apana encounters a curious mix of cops, Federal agents, politicians, union officials, ragtag criminals, whistleblowers, stage actors, screen directors, triathletes, as well as Kay’s also-missing boyfriend, lawyer turned lifeguard Matthew Serrano. Apana’s pursuit of leads takes him all over O`ahu: from the metro downtown area, to the Windward and Leeward coasts, to the fabled North Shore, and to places far beyond. It also takes him back in years as he revisits the Lino Johnson murder and discovers how much he had missed the first time around.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aMissing personsvFiction. 0aPrivate investigatorszHawaiivFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package 2014-2016z978311056413608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066323540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082485885840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824858858423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824858858.jpg  a978-3-11-056413-6  UHP eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066323-5  University of Hawaii Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK